    bin/Debug/net8.0/Insights/fixtures/r2/.

    DECISIONS:
    - Format: plain text (.txt) — matches r1 fixture convention (sample-*.txt); .txt is
      the natural format for legal prose and easy for both AiAnalysisNodeExecutor (which
      reads document body as string) and human eyeballing during fixture review.
    - Content style: LLM-assisted realistic legal prose (60-250 lines per fixture). All
      party names, jurisdictions, monetary amounts, GUIDs, USPTO application numbers,
      and personal identifiers are fabricated. No PII; no real client data.
    - Location: tests/Insights/fixtures/r2/{area}/ instead of the POML's suggested
      projects/.../notes/test-data/ — because the existing r1 test-fixture pattern already
      lives at tests/Insights/fixtures/ with csproj wiring. POML allows "a more permanent
      test fixture location per project convention" — this satisfies that.
    - Gate-fail CTRNS×NDA included as one of the 3 CTRNS matter fixtures (matches
      design-a3 §5.2 example 5).
    - Routing-fallback uncovered fixture added beyond mandatory 18 (covers task description
      bullet #6 about uncovered pairs for Wave D4 / task 033 testing).
    - D5-Q1 (sprk_project primary attribute) empirically resolved: actual attribute is
      sprk_projectname, NOT sprk_name (the resolver's ReadColumns list still has
      "sprk_name" — that's a separate concern for D5 follow-up; sprk_name is presumably
      a different attribute used by the resolver intentionally).

    QUALITY GATES:
    - Build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/: 0 errors, 15 warnings (all pre-existing,
      none introduced — task touched no src/ files)
